<h2>Let there be light!</h2>
<p>I had a little play with the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceLightEvent" rel="external">devicelight api</a> last night.</p>
<p>As you imagine, this relatively new api obtains the amount of light from the surrounding atmosphere of your device and returns a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lux" rel="external">lux level</a> for you to play with.</p>
<p>Here I just added a <em>devicelight</em> event listener to the window of my experiment and switch CSS theme based on if it's light or dark!</p>
<h2>Current support</h2>
<p>Support for this api is scarce at the moment:</p>
<blockquote class="pullquote" cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceLightEvent">The devicelight event is implemented and preference enabled by default in Firefox Mobile for Android (15.0) and in Firefox OS (B2G). Starting with Gecko 22.0 (Firefox 22.0 / Thunderbird 22.0 / SeaMonkey 2.19) a desktop implementation for Mac OS X is also available. Support for Windows 7 is in progress.</blockquote>
<p>But I think it could be a useful feature and hopefully it'll be more widely supported in the near future.</p>
