<p>Be sure to check it out in <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/" rel="external">Firefox</a> and turn your light on and off to see it in action. Or just cover your device camera, to avoid looking like a mad man turning your light on and off and on and off...</p>
<small>Tip: try it in quite a bright environment to see the sun, cover up your light detection to see the moon!</small>
<h2>Practical uses</h2>
<p>So I know my demo is a bit gimmicky but when the devicelight api is more widely supported I'm going to try and switch an entire website theme based on the light a user is viewing it in.</p>
<p>Perhaps a bit more subtly though - for instance toning down the brighter colours on a web page to aid readability and also to avoid screen burn for those high res screens you've all got!</p>
<p>If you have any ideas of use for this kind of thing let me know, grab the <a href="https://github.com/furzeface/LetThereBeLight" rel="external">source code on GitHub</a> and have a little go if you like.</p>
